Text.Value: No idea. Our post is out here. Besides his chosen swords, Head Banker Glitterbeard doesn't like us asking what goes on below.
Got notions, don't you? Pity you don't have the coin to back them up.
Where can I get one?
Well, if she got paid, you can be damn sure I will too. Go on.
Is this... why Glitterbeard's been acting so strangely?
Full privacy when you're down there, right? No guards poking about, and walls thick enough to drown a banshee's wail.
Ah, you speak of the Stone Lord? No, no - he only looked, sounded, and quite possibly smelled exactly like Minsc.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Ah, I see - you've made an understandable mistake'

Text.Value: Hope you had a fruitful visit, saer. But - that's your business, of course.

EditorData.NodeContext: Polite, friendly - second line is nervously rushing to assure us he wasn't prying. The upper crust don't appreciate spreading their bank business around.

Text.Value: Just need to see your vault pass, please.
Leave.
Do you accept cash instead? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
You really shouldn't be down here without a vault pass.
I'd be running the other way - but go on, then. Your funeral.
You work for that mean bastard and you turn up late?
Here you are.
That... won't be necessary. Go ahead.

EditorData.NodeContext: absolutely confused, wants you out of the way

Text.Value: It's just us down here. No one to judge you for choosing life over 'duty'.
Mate. Just go and get a bloody vault pass.
Best pretend I didn't hear that.
I just showed it to you, don't you remember? Are you feeling all right?
Looks in order. Blessed day to you.
Then you'll show it again. Vault. Pass.
And they still needed a vault pass.
Hah. No one to see your corpse slip into the bay, either. We've built a chute for just that purpose.
Walk away.
Wait - didn't the Head Banker already take you down?
What can I expect below?
A needful sniff, perhaps? So you know I am no impostor?

EditorData.NodeContext: Raising an armpit speculatively, all very helpful

Text.Value: The city depends on me getting down there. I really don't have time to explain.
That lot looked half-rabid - had Glitterbeard all aflutter.
You shouldn't even be down here without one. Talk to Meadhoney - upstairs.
Did you actually buy your way past Faril?
For... security, I expect.
Just... don't let Glitterbeard see you, right?
I'm with the group that came down just before me.
You did? Oh, sorry - things have been hectic. Go on ahead.

EditorData.NodeContext: bit addled, doesn't remember the player showing his pass, but doesn't want to admit it either

Text.Value: Go, then. I might be out of my head, but... gods help me, I believe you.

Synopsis: The player approaches the vault guard and is asked to present their bank pass.
